Jeanette Chabalala, News24SA police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A 14-year-old Free State boy has died after he was repeatedly assaulted with a sjambok by his uncle and neighbour in Thaba Nchu on Tuesday, police said.He had allegedly stolen R500 from his grandmother, said police spokesperson Sergeant Martin Xuma.&ldquo;It is alleged that the grandmother noticed that her money was missing and suspected that his grandson Amogelang Mokgothu stole the money,&rdquo; Xuma said on Thursday.&ldquo;The boy&rsquo;s uncle and the neighbour found him and brought him home where they allegedly beat him with a sjambok.&rdquo;Xuma said the two allegedly assaulted the boy while he was tied to a laundry line. He was left outside over night and was found dead on Wednesday morning.His 30-year-old uncle and 22-year-old neighbour were arrested for the murder.They are expected to appear in the Thaba Nchu Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Thursday.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.